  "content": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "1. System Requirement"
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/How%20to%20Implement%20ICU%20by%20SAIL_IO/image-2024-11-19_17-51-30.png?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/How to Implement ICU by SAIL_IO/image-2024-11-19_17-51-30.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "E52142A pin description"
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "headers": [
        "",
        "Description"
      ],
      "rows": [
        [
          "RFC",
          "Pin RFC indicates IC communication state, only high if communication on SPI and DSI is possible SAIL need to detect raising edge to start SPI communication. (RFC is high should be check)"
        ],
        [
          "DCR1B",
          "DSI3 channel 1 ready bar output (active low) Internal pull up, open drain"
        ],
        [
          "DCR2B",
          "DSI3 channel 2 ready bar output (active low) Internal pull up, open drain"
        ]
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "2. Overview"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The GPIO driver also supports receiving interrupts from GPIO. Interrupts are generated as level triggered, rising edge, falling edge, or dual edge triggered."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Before any GPIO interrupt is received, it is configured and enabled at both the generic interrupt controller (GIC) and the top-level mode multiplexer (TLMM) hardware."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "MCAL from Qualcomm can't support ICU now, we have to implement it by ourselves."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "How many SAIL_IO can used to detect edge? Is there any pin which are not support ICU?"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "3. Port configuration"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "PortPinDirection should be defined as PORT_PIN_IN."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "PortPinMode should be defined as PORT_MODE_GENERAL_PURPOSE"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Note that more than one mode is allowed by default. That way it is e.g. possible to combine DIO with another mode such as ICU."
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/How%20to%20Implement%20ICU%20by%20SAIL_IO/image-2024-11-19_17-9-39.png?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/How to Implement ICU by SAIL_IO/image-2024-11-19_17-9-39.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "4. Interrupt configuration"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        "Overview"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "summary_irq_rtcu collect all the GPIO interrupts. The direct connect is designed to provide a low-latency interrupt to processors that are running at higher frequencies."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "How to map the dir_conn_irq_rtcu_0 to a SAIL_IO?"
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "headers": [
        "Core",
        "Interrupt",
        "Trigger",
        "Source Subsystem",
        "Source Instance",
        "Destination Instance",
        "Vector"
      ],
      "rows": [
        [
          "u_sailss_tlmm_glue",
          "summary_irq_rtcu",
          "Varies",
          "Safety Island",
          "u_sailss",
          "u_sailss",
          "572"
        ],
        [
          "u_sailss_tlmm_glue",
          "dir_conn_irq_rtcu_0~21",
          "Varies",
          "Safety Island",
          "u_sailss",
          "u_sailss",
          "573:592 570:571"
        ]
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        "GIC configuration"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "We need register interrupt in the generic interrupt controller (GIC), this will be done in OS."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Before any GPIO interrupt is received, it is configured and enabled at both the generic interrupt controller (GIC) and the top-level mode multiplexer (TLMM) hardware."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The interrupt at GIC is enabled during the TLMM driver initialization as it is not GPIO-specific."
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/How%20to%20Implement%20ICU%20by%20SAIL_IO/image-2024-11-19_17-15-14.png?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/How to Implement ICU by SAIL_IO/image-2024-11-19_17-15-14.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Isr function shall clear the corresponding register."
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/How%20to%20Implement%20ICU%20by%20SAIL_IO/image-2024-11-19_17-40-45.png?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/How to Implement ICU by SAIL_IO/image-2024-11-19_17-40-45.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        "TLMM configuration"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "This should be done during initialization."
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/How%20to%20Implement%20ICU%20by%20SAIL_IO/image-2024-11-19_17-34-58.png?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/How to Implement ICU by SAIL_IO/image-2024-11-19_17-34-58.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "5. Test result"
